{"id":"1511.08069","submitter":"Changpeng Shao","authors":"Changpeng Shao","title":"An Improvement of Rota's Straightening Algorithm","comments":"26 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In bracket algebra, the calculation of invariant division and invariant\nGr\\\"{o}bner basis proposed in \\cite{li 2014} rely on straightening algorithm.\nUntil now, there are at least three different types of straightening\nalgorithms, among which Rota's straightening algorithm has the best efficiency.\nHowever, there exists a flaw in Rota's straightening algorithm, i.e., it needs\nfind all the straight bracket monomials with the same content as the input\nbeforehand, which is quite difficult. So in this paper, we will propose a new\nstraightening algorithm based on dual bracket, which is a new concept of Young\ntableau. In this new straightening algorithm, we only need to find a few number\nof straight bracket monomials in each step instead of finding them all in one\nstep. And so it is an improvement of Rota's straightening algorithm. According\nto our tests, this new straightening algorithm reflects more advantages when\nthe dimension and the degree increase. Moreover, this straightening algorithm\nstill works when Rota's straightening algorithm fails.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 14:15:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2018 13:59:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-12"}
